Package civitas.celestis.util.tuple

Interface IntTuple<T extends IntTuple<T>>

Type Parameters:
T - The tuple itself (used as the parameter and result of various operations)
All Superinterfaces:
Iterable<Integer>, Serializable, Tuple<Integer>
All Known Implementing Classes:
Int2, Int3, Int4
public interface IntTuple<T extends IntTuple<T>> extends Tuple<Integer>
An integer-typed tuple whose values are stored using primitive ints. Integer tuples have similar characteristics to Vectors in that they natively support various arithmetic operations.
